#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1858
msgid "Preparing for the next release"
msgstr "Forberedelse af den næste udgivelse"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1860
msgid ""
"After the upgrade there are several things you can do to prepare for the "
"next release."
msgstr ""
"Efter opgraderingen er der nogle ting, du kan forberede for din næste "
"udgivelse."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1866
msgid ""
"Remove obsolete and unused packages as described in <xref linkend=\"obsolete"
"\"/>.  You should review which configuration files they use and consider "
"purging the packages to remove their configuration files."
msgstr ""
"Fjern forældede og ubrugte pakker som beskrevet i <xref linkend=\"obsolete"
"\"/>. Du bør gennemgå hvilke konfigurationsfiler de bruger og overveje at "
"fjerne pakkerne så deres konfigurationsfiler forsvinder."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1874
msgid "Upgrade to GRUB 2"
msgstr "Opgradering til GRUB 2"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1876
msgid ""
"During the upgrade, you will normally have been offered the option to "
"\"chainload\" GRUB 2: that is, to keep GRUB Legacy as the primary boot "
"loader but to add an option to it to load GRUB 2 and then start your "
"&debian; system from that.  This allows you to verify that GRUB 2 works on "
"your system before committing to use it permanently."
msgstr ""
"Under opgraderingen, vil du normalt være blevet tilbudt muligheden "
"for at »chainload« GRUB 2: Det vil sige, at bevare GRUB Legacy som den "
"primære opstartsindlæser, men tilføje en mulighed for at indlæse GRUB 2 "
"og så starte dit &debian;-system fra den. Dette giver dig mulighed for at "
"verificere at GRUB 2 fungerer på dit system før du binder dig til at "
"bruge den permanent."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1883
msgid ""
"Once you have confirmed that GRUB 2 works, you should switch to using it "
"properly: the chainloading setup is only intended to be used temporarily.  "
"You can do this by running <command>upgrade-from-grub-legacy</command>."
msgstr ""
"Når du har bekræftet at GRUB 2 fungerer, så bør du skifte til den "
"permanent: Opsætningen med chainloading (kædeindlæsning) er kun lavet "
"som en midlertidig løsning. Du kan skifte ved at køre "
"<command>upgrade-from-grub-legacy</command>."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1888
msgid ""
"The GRUB Manual has <ulink url=\"http://www.gnu.org/software/grub/manual/"
"grub.html#Changes-from-GRUB-Legacy\">more information</ulink> on the changes "
"between GRUB Legacy and GRUB 2, some of which may require changes to complex "
"configurations.  If you have not modified your boot loader configuration, "
"you should not need to do anything further."
msgstr ""
"GRUB-manualen har <ulink url=\"http://www.gnu.org/software/grub/manual/"
"grub.html#Changes-from-GRUB-Legacy\">yderligere information</ulink> om "
"ændringerne mellem GRUB Legacy og GRUB 2, hvoraf nogle kan kræve "
"ændringer for komplekse konfigurationer. Hvis du ikke har ændret din "
"konfiguration af opstartsindlæseren, så skal du ikke gøre andet."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1900
msgid "Deprecated components"
msgstr "Forældede komponenter"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1902
msgid ""
"With the next release of &debian; &nextrelease; (codenamed "
"&nextreleasename;) some features will be deprecated. Users will need to "
"migrate to other alternatives to prevent trouble when updating to "
"&nextrelease;."
msgstr ""
"Med den næste udgivelse af &debian; &nextrelease; (kodenavn "
"&nextreleasename;) vil nogle funktioner blive forældet. Brugere "
"vil skulle migrere til andre alternativer for at forhindre "
"problemer under opgradering til &nextrelease;."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1909
msgid "This includes the following features:"
msgstr "Dette inkluderer de følgende funktioner:"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1922
msgid "Obsolete packages"
msgstr "Forældede pakker"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><footnote><para>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1928
msgid ""
"Or for as long as there is not another release in that time frame.  "
"Typically only two stable releases are supported at any given time."
msgstr ""
"Eller i den periode hvor der endnu ikke er en ny udgivelse. Typisk "
"er kun to stabile udgivelser understøttet på samme tidspunkt."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1924
msgid ""
"Introducing several thousand new packages, &releasename; also retires and "
"omits more than four thousand old packages that were in &oldreleasename;.  "
"It provides no upgrade path for these obsolete packages.  While nothing "
"prevents you from continuing to use an obsolete package where desired, the "
"Debian project will usually discontinue security support for it a year after "
"&releasename;'s release<placeholder type=\"footnote\" id=\"0\"/>, and will "
"not normally provide other support in the meantime.  Replacing them with "
"available alternatives, if any, is recommended."
msgstr ""
"Der introduceres flere tusinde nye pakker i &releasename;, men fjernes og "
"udelades også fire hundrede gamle pakker, som var i &oldreleasename;. "
"Der tilbydese ingen opgraderingssti for disse forældede pakker. Selv om "
"intet forhindrer dig i fortsat at benytte en forældet pakke, så vil "
"Debianprojektet normat ikke fortsætte den sikkerhedsmæssige support af "
"pakken mere end et år efter &releasename;s udgivelse"
"<placeholder type=\"footnote\" id=\"0\"/>, og vil normalt heller ikke "
"tilbyde anden støtte i mellemperioden. Erstatning af dem med tilgængelige "
"alternativer, hvis sådanne findes, anbefales."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1935
msgid ""
"There are many reasons why packages might have been removed from the "
"distribution: they are no longer maintained upstream; there is no longer a "
"Debian Developer interested in maintaining the packages; the functionality "
"they provide has been superseded by different software (or a new version); "
"or they are no longer considered suitable for &releasename; due to bugs in "
"them.  In the latter case, packages might still be present in the "
"<quote>unstable</quote> distribution."
msgstr ""
"Der kan være mange årsager til at pakker er blevet fjernet fra distributionen: "
"De bliver ikke længere vedligeholdt opstrøms, der er ikke længere en "
"Debianudvikler interesseret i at vedligeholde pakkerne; funktionaliteten "
"de tilbyder er blevet efterfulgt af andre programmer (eller en ny version); "
"eller de anses ikke længere for at være egnet for &releasename; på grund af "
"fejl i dem. I det sidste tilfælde, kan pakker stadig være til stede i "
"distributionen <quote>unstable</quote>."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1943
msgid ""
"Detecting which packages in an updated system are <quote>obsolete</quote> is "
"easy since the package management front-ends will mark them as such.  If you "
"are using <command>aptitude</command>, you will see a listing of these "
"packages in the <quote>Obsolete and Locally Created Packages</quote> entry.  "
"<command>dselect</command> provides a similar section but the listing it "
"presents might differ."
msgstr ""
"Detektering af hvilke pakker på et opdateret system som er <quote>obsolete</quote> "
"(forældet) er meget nemt da pakkehåndteringernes brugerflader vil markere "
"dem som sådan. Hvis du bruger <command>aptitude</command>, så vil du se en "
"liste over disse pakker under punktet <quote>Forældede og lokalt oprettede "
"pakker</quote>. <command>dselect</command> tilbyder et lignende afsnit, men "
"listen der vises kan være forskellig."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1950
msgid ""
"Also, if you have used <command>aptitude</command> or <command>apt-get</"
"command> to manually install packages in &oldreleasename; it will have kept "
"track of those packages you manually installed and will be able to mark as "
"obsolete those packages pulled in by dependencies alone which are no longer "
"needed if a package has been removed.  <command>aptitude</command> and "
"<systemitem role=\"package\">apt</systemitem>, unlike <command>deborphan</"
"command>, will not mark for removal packages that you manually installed, as "
"opposed to those that were automatically installed through dependencies.  To "
"remove automatically installed packages that are no longer used, run:"
msgstr ""
"Hvis du har brugt <command>aptitude</command> eller <command>apt-get</"
"command> til manuelt at installere pakker i &oldreleasename; vil programmet "
"have styr på hvilke pakker du har installeret manuelt og vil kunne markere "
"som forældet på de pakker der er trukket ind af afhængigheder alene og som "
"ikke længere er krævet hvis en pakke er blevet fjernet. "
"<command>aptitude</command> og <systemitem role=\"package\">apt</systemitem>, "
"til forskel fra <command>deborphan</command>, vil ikke markere pakker til "
"fjernelse, hvis du har installeret dem manuelt, til forskel fra dem som blev "
"installeret automatisk via afhængigheder. For at fjerne automatisk "
"installerede pakker som ikke længere bruges, kør:"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><screen>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1962
#, no-wrap
msgid "# apt-get autoremove\n"
msgstr "# apt-get autoremove\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/upgrading.dbk:1965
msgid ""
"There are additional tools you can use to find obsolete packages such as "
"<command>deborphan</command>, <command>debfoster</command> or "
"<command>cruft</command>.  <command>deborphan</command> is highly "
"recommended, although it will (in default mode) only report obsolete "
"libraries: packages in the <quote><literal>libs</literal></quote> or "
"<quote><literal>oldlibs</literal></quote> sections that are not used by any "
"other packages.  Do not blindly remove the packages these tools present, "
"especially if you are using aggressive non-default options that are prone to "
"produce false positives.  It is highly recommended that you manually review "
"the packages suggested for removal (i.e.  their contents, size and "
"description) before you remove them."
msgstr ""
"Der er yderligere værktøjer, som du kan bruge til at finde forældede "
"pakker såsom <command>deborphan</command>, <command>debfoster</command> eller "
"<command>cruft</command>. <command>deborphan</command> anbefales kraftigt, "
"selvom programmet kun vil (i standardtilstand) rapportere forældede "
"biblioteker: Pakker i <quote><literal>libs</literal></quote> eller "
"<quote><literal>oldlibs</literal></quote> afsnit som ikke bruges af nogen "
"andre pakker. Fjern ikke blindt pakkerne disse værktøjer præsenterer, "
"specielt hvis du bruger aggressive indstillinger, der ikke er standard, "
"som er mere udsat for at give falske positive resultater. Det anbefales "
"stærkt at du manuelt gennemser pakkerne foreslåes for fjernelse (dvs. "
"deres indhold, størrelse og beskrivelse) før du fjerner dem."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
